The exponent of the nonlinearity, $\alpha$, has been associated with trap-limited transport when the trap energies follow an exponential density of states.\cite{Mark1962} The reader should note that the MC at constant voltage increases linearly (to first order) with $\alpha$. Therefore, any process that increases $\alpha$ will likely increase the observed MC. This ``$\alpha$-enhancement" allows MFE at constant voltage to significantly exceed the 100\% maximum predicted by our theory for the constant-current effect.




